[I have known John for a number of years and have found him to be objective
and reliable in his comments and views. To date we have been unable to get
the Australian military viewpoint, report, or comments on these events,
only that of Australian journalists. It would be appreciated if we could
have their (fuller) account of what happened. Personally I have found the
discomfort from the US BioPort anthrax vaccine to be trivial on any scale
-- ditto my students -- and a dream compared to typhoid, plague, or the old
egg-adapted rabies vaccines, but I was born in a different age. I have no
experience of the British vaccine. Unfortunately, news is what the media
says it is, and one should always remember that the primary purpose of
newspapers and TV is not objectivity, but selling advertising for
groceries. - Mod.MHJ]
